{
  "texts": [
    "Longer trajectory lengths and higher cumulative rewards demonstrate the model's ability to maximize long-term engagement.",
    "However, it is important to note that a higher average reward is not necessarily better.",
    "Excessively high average rewards may indicate a model's overemphasis on immediate responses.",
    "Baselines.To comprehensively and fairly evaluate the superiority of our proposed BiLLP, we choose some representative RL-based methods and LLM-based methods as baselines.",
    "For the RLbased methods, we choose seven representative baselines including the State-Of-The-Art (SOTA) method for long-term engagement optimization to mitigate filter bubble problems:• DQN, or Deep Q-Networks [34], is a deep reinforcement learning algorithm that combines deep neural networks with the Qlearning algorithm."
  ]
